  "texts": [
    "Since V 0 is finite-dimensional, there is only a finite number of elements i ∈ I d for which n i is nonzero.",
    "Furthermore, since the grading is locally constant, n i only depends on the connected component ⟨q⟩ of I containing i, and we set n ⟨q⟩:= n i.",
    "Definition 2.2.",
    "An irregular class is a function Θ: π 0 (I) → N with finite support.",
    "The dimensions n i of the graded pieces thus define an irregular class Θ associated to V 0."
